The paper deals with spectrum sensing in cognitive radio, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of random matrix theory suggests that the paper could also belong to the category of numerical analysis (cs.NI). The paper also presents numerical simulations, which could place it in the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or applied mathematics (cs.MA).
